Simple command line utility that displays file contents in binary.
Similar to the popular Unix utility hexdump.

Example usage...

$ binarydump hello.txt 
0x0    01001000   01100101   01101100   01101100   
0x4    01101111   00101100   00100000   01010111   
0x8    01101111   01110010   01101100   01100100   
0xC    00100001   00100000   01010100   01101000   
0x10   01101001   01110011   00100000   01101001   
0x14   01110011   00100000   01100001   01101110   
0x18   00100000   01100101   01111000   01100001   
0x1C   01101101   01110000   01101100   01100101   
0x20   00101110   00001010   
0x22
